main event: A UFO sighting of an oblong silver object with black stripes observed in Brainerd, Minnesota on November 14, 1956.
interesting points: The object was the size of a basketball and was seen descending,The sighting lasted for one minute,There was a lack of sufficient data to conclude definitively what the object was,The report suggested it could possibly be a balloon or aircraft,The weather conditions were cloudy at the time of the sighting.
sighted object: an oblong silver object with black stripes
witness description: George Fklp, 53 years old, a civilian observer driving an automobile.
